# Anti-Patterns — Forbidden

Full standard: [docs/agent/standards/common/anti-patterns.md](../../docs/agent/standards/common/anti-patterns.md)

## Fat Controllers
❌ Business logic in controllers — validation, DB queries, transformations.
✅ Controllers call exactly one service method and return the result.

## Swallowed Errors
❌ `catch (e) { console.log(e); }` — errors silently absorbed.
✅ Either handle specifically (typed error) or re-throw. Always log with `requestId` context.

## Any Types
❌ `const x: any = ...` or implicit `any` parameters.
✅ Use `unknown` + type guard, or the specific type. `eslint: @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` is an error.

## Cross-Domain Imports
❌ `import { JobsService } from '../jobs/JobsService'` inside the applications domain.
✅ Import from barrels only. If you need a type from another domain, it belongs in `src/core/`.

## Raw Error Strings
❌ `throw new Error('Job not found')`
✅ `throw new NotFoundError('Job', id)` — typed errors with structured context.

## Synchronous Blocking in Async Context
❌ `fs.readFileSync(...)` or CPU-intensive work on the event loop.
✅ Use async I/O. Offload CPU work to BullMQ workers.

## Unguarded BullMQ Workers
❌ Workers that process without error handling — one bad job crashes the worker.
✅ `try/catch` on every job; move to dead-letter queue on N failures.

## Prisma Queries Outside Services
❌ `prisma.job.findMany()` directly in a controller.
✅ All Prisma calls inside service methods only.

## Missing Pagination
❌ `findAll()` returning an unbounded array.
✅ All list methods accept a `page` + `pageSize` parameter and return `{ data, meta }`.
